The paper deals with the problem of indexing a string to report the occurrences of a query pattern containing wildcards. This problem is related to data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR), as it involves efficient search and retrieval of information. The paper also introduces new techniques, which could be of independent interest, indicating a possible connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of indexing a string, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG).
